Boothroyd’s side face hosts Holland in Heerenveen on Saturday and he is expecting another tough test.

He added: ‘We all know the pedigree of players the Dutch produce and the good attacking football they always like to play,' he said.

'We’re here to compete and we need to get some refuelling done. A couple of days’ rest and then we go again.'

 

